## Overview
Minecraft allows players to use written books (`WrittenBook`) and writable books (`BookMeta`). This lesson covers how to create and give a simple custom book.

### Creating a Simple Book
```java
import org.bukkit.Material;
import org.bukkit.entity.Player;
import org.bukkit.inventory.ItemStack;
import org.bukkit.inventory.meta.BookMeta;

public void giveCustomBook(Player player) {
    ItemStack book = new ItemStack(Material.WRITTEN_BOOK);
    BookMeta meta = (BookMeta) book.getItemMeta();
    meta.setTitle("Secrets of the Realm");
    meta.setAuthor("DungeonMaster");
    meta.addPage("Welcome to the secret realm!", "Use this knowledge wisely.");
    book.setItemMeta(meta);
    player.getInventory().addItem(book);
}
```

### Giving the Book to a Player via Command
```java
if (command.getName().equalsIgnoreCase("givebook")) {
    giveCustomBook(player);
    player.sendMessage("§aYou received a custom book!");
}
```

## Overview
Books can contain formatted text, colors, and lore to make them more engaging.

### Colored Text Example
```java
import net.kyori.adventure.text.Component;
import net.kyori.adventure.text.format.TextColor;

meta.addPage(
    Component.text("§6Chapter 1: Secrets", TextColor.color(0xFFD700)),
    Component.text("§7This book contains hidden knowledge.")
);
```

### Adding Lore
```java
meta.lore(Arrays.asList(
    Component.text("Legendary Book"),
    Component.text("Read carefully")
));
book.setItemMeta(meta);
```

## Overview
Using Adventure API, you can make clickable text in books that execute commands or suggest text.

### Clickable Text Example
```java
import net.kyori.adventure.text.Component;
import net.kyori.adventure.text.event.ClickEvent;

Component page = Component.text("Click here to teleport")
    .clickEvent(ClickEvent.runCommand("/warp secret"));
meta.addPage(page);
book.setItemMeta(meta);
```

## Overview
You can combine multiple features: colors, clickable text, lore, and give the books dynamically.

### Full Example
```java
ItemStack book = new ItemStack(Material.WRITTEN_BOOK);
BookMeta meta = (BookMeta) book.getItemMeta();
meta.setTitle("Adventurer's Guide");
meta.setAuthor("QuestMaster");
meta.lore(Arrays.asList(
    Component.text("Epic Book"),
    Component.text("Contains secrets and quests")
));
meta.addPage(
    Component.text("Chapter 1: The Beginning\nClick here to teleport")
        .clickEvent(ClickEvent.runCommand("/warp start"))
        .color(TextColor.color(0x00FF00))
);
book.setItemMeta(meta);
player.getInventory().addItem(book);
player.sendMessage("§aYou received the Adventurer's Guide!");
```
